.SH "NAME"
systemadm \- Graphical frontend for the systemd system and session manager
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'\fBsystemadm\ \fR\fB[OPTIONS...]\fR\ 'u
\fBsystemadm \fR\fB[OPTIONS...]\fR
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
\fBsystemadm\fR
is a graphical frontend for the systemd system and session manager and allows introspection and control of systemd\&.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.PP
The following options are understood:
.PP
\fB\-\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
.RS 4
Prints a short help text and exits\&.
.RE
.PP
\fB\-\-system\fR
.RS 4
Connect to the systemd system manager\&. (Default)
.RE
.PP
\fB\-\-session\fR
.RS 4
Connect to the systemd session manager of the calling user\&.
.RE
.PP
In addition to this a number of parameters common to all Gtk+ programs are supported\&.
